Subject: Re: KT Document for CRS and Auto-Cancellation Batch Process

Dear Teja,

Regarding the KT document for the CRS work and the Auto-Cancellation batch process in Forward Contract, I would like to clarify that the Auto Cancellation logic is straightforward and works the same way as the old functionality.

Below is the complete logic involved:

1. Auto-Cancellation Batch Trigger

If DUE_DT_CONTRACT < SYSDATE, then the PSO team will run the following two .sh files:
	1.	/TFEEAPP/base_domain/Reports/SrcScripts/auto_can_normal.sh
	2.	/TFEEAPP/base_domain/Reports/SrcScripts/auto_can_cross.sh

After running these scripts, the transaction becomes available in the Merging queue.
Once the merging is completed, the transaction will appear in the Auto Cancellation batch based on the SQL condition below.

2. Auto-Cancellation SQL Condition

A transaction enters the Auto-Cancellation queue if:

C_TRX_STATUS = 'M'
AND BAL_FRGN_AMT > 0
AND CAN_FLG = '3'
AND C_FUNC_SHORT_NAME IN 
('Book_FC_BRU','Booking_FC_DEO','DLIVERY_BRU','DLIVERY_DEO',
 'FWCO_CANCEL_BRU','MANUAL_CNLDEO_TF','FWCO_FC_RFO','Sub_CE_15TF')
AND C_FUNC_SHORT_NAME <> 'autocanTF'
AND T_SYS_REL_TIME = TRUNC(SYSDATE)

3. TASK.js

I have written the required logic in TASK.js.
Once you review the TASK.js file, the flow will be clear.

Since these are the only conditions involved in Auto Cancellation, there isn‚Äôt much more content to include in a detailed KT document.

